apt-notifier (1.0-3mlrepo2) mepis; urgency=low

  * Repackaged For Mepis 8.5

 -- Paul Brooks <maintainer@mepiscommunity.org>  Wed, 02 Jun 2010 22:31:47 +1200

apt-notifier (1.0-3mlrepo1) mepis; urgency=low

  * Incorporated changes Davo requested.
  *
  * a) Added Singleshot timer added in python script
  *    to get Popup message lined up over icon.
  *
  * b) Deleted "X-KDE-autostart-after=panel" and
  *    "X-DBUS-StartupType=Unique" lines from the 
  *    apt-notifier-autostart.desktop file. They
  *    don't belong in a KDE4 .desktop file.
  *
  * c) Added lines near bottom of python script 
  *    "if AptNotify.isSessionRestored():"
  *    "    sys.exit(1)"
  *    to prevent start up of multiple notifiers
  *
  * d) In /usr/bin/apt-notifier-unhide-Icon script
  *    disabled the code that kills any running
  *    notifiers because its now handled in the python
  *    script by item c.
  *
  * e) In python script
  *
  *    replaced "/usr/lib/kde4/libexec/kdesu" 
  *    with "/usr/bin/su-to-root -X -c"
  *
  *    replaced "konsole -e apt-get upgrade"
  *    with "x-terminal-emulator -e apt-get upgrade"
  *
  *    These changes are to make the notifier more
  *    generic some possibly it can be used with antix.
  *
  *
  * My own changes.
  *
  * a) Pulled the apt-notifier-check-Updates script
  *    back into the python script.
  *
  * b) Added a "-e 'freed.'" line in the check_updates
  *    section to catch the case where upgrades free up
  *    space rather than take more space. Without this 
  *    change the number of upgrades shown is one greater
  *    than what it actually is.
  *
  * c) Deleted the X-KDE-* and X-DBUS-* lines from the
  *    apt-notifier-menu.desktop file. Seems to
  *    work without them.
  
 -- Kent Mathern <maintainer@mepiscommunity.org>  Tue, 01 Jun 2010 09:30:38 -0400

apt-notifier (1.0-2mlrepo2) mepis; urgency=low

